      "value": {
        "latex": "La fonction $\\Argch$ est définie sur $[1,+\\infty[$. Or\n\\begin{eqnarray*}\n\\frac{1}{2}\\left(x+\\frac{1}{x}\\right)\\ge 1\n &\\Longleftrightarrow&\\frac{x^2+1}{x}\\ge 2\\\\\n &\\Longleftrightarrow&\\frac{x^2+1-2x}{x}\\ge 0\\\\\n &\\Longleftrightarrow&\\frac{(x-1)^2}{x}\\ge 0\\\\\n &\\Longleftrightarrow& x > 0 \n\\end{eqnarray*}\ndonc $f$ est définie sur $]0,+\\infty[$. \n\n\\medskip\n\nSoit $x>0$, alors $y=\\frac{1}{2}\\left(x+\\frac{1}{x}\\right)\\ge 1$\net on sait que $\\Argch y=\\ln(y+\\sqrt{y^2-1})$. Ainsi\n$\\sqrt{y^2-1}=\\sqrt{\\frac{1}{4}\\left(x+\\frac{1}{x}\\right)^2-1}\n=\\sqrt{\\frac{(x^2+1)^2}{4x^2}-1}=\\sqrt{\\frac{(x^2-1)^2}{4x^2}}\n=\\left|\\frac{x^2-1}{2x}\\right|$,\non obtient\n$$f(x)=\\Argch y=\\ln(y+\\sqrt{y^2-1})=\\ln\\left(\\frac{x^2+1}{2x}+\\left|\\frac{x^2-1}{2x}\\right|\\right)$$\n\n\nOn a supposé $x>0$, il suffit donc de distinguer les cas $x\\ge 1$ et $0<x\\le 1$.\n\\begin{itemize}\n  \\item Si $x\\ge 1$, $\\displaystyle f(x)=\\ln\\left(\\frac{x^2+1}{2x}+\\frac{x^2-1}{2x}\\right)=\\ln x$.\n  \\item Si $0<x\\le 1$, $\\displaystyle f(x)=\\ln\\left(\\frac{x^2+1}{2x}+\\frac{1-x^2}{2x}\\right)=\\ln \\frac{1}{x}=-\\ln x$.\n\\end{itemize}\n\nPuisque $\\ln x$ est positif si $x\\ge 1$ et négatif si $x\\le 1$, \non obtient dans les deux cas $f(x)=|\\ln x|$.\n\n\\begin{center}\n__TIKZ_2eb3cf85-ccec-41b4-a1aa-14e619f858b0__  \n\\end{center}",
        "html": "<p>La fonction <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Argch\\)</span> est définie\nsur <span class=\"math inline\">\\([1,+\\infty[\\)</span>. Or <span\nclass=\"math display\">\\[\\begin{aligned}\n\\frac{1}{2}\\left(x+\\frac{1}{x}\\right)\\ge 1\n&amp;\\Longleftrightarrow&amp;\\frac{x^2+1}{x}\\ge 2\\\\\n&amp;\\Longleftrightarrow&amp;\\frac{x^2+1-2x}{x}\\ge 0\\\\\n&amp;\\Longleftrightarrow&amp;\\frac{(x-1)^2}{x}\\ge 0\\\\\n&amp;\\Longleftrightarrow&amp; x &gt; 0\n\\end{aligned}\\]</span> donc <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f\\)</span> est\ndéfinie sur <span class=\"math inline\">\\(]0,+\\infty[\\)</span>.</p>\n<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x&gt;0\\)</span>, alors <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(y=\\frac{1}{2}\\left(x+\\frac{1}{x}\\right)\\ge\n1\\)</span> et on sait que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Argch\ny=\\ln(y+\\sqrt{y^2-1})\\)</span>. Ainsi <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\sqrt{y^2-1}=\\sqrt{\\frac{1}{4}\\left(x+\\frac{1}{x}\\right)^2-1}\n=\\sqrt{\\frac{(x^2+1)^2}{4x^2}-1}=\\sqrt{\\frac{(x^2-1)^2}{4x^2}}\n=\\left|\\frac{x^2-1}{2x}\\right|\\)</span>, on obtient <span\nclass=\"math display\">\\[f(x)=\\Argch\ny=\\ln(y+\\sqrt{y^2-1})=\\ln\\left(\\frac{x^2+1}{2x}+\\left|\\frac{x^2-1}{2x}\\right|\\right)\\]</span></p>\n<p>On a supposé <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x&gt;0\\)</span>, il suffit\ndonc de distinguer les cas <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x\\ge 1\\)</span>\net <span class=\"math inline\">\\(0&lt;x\\le 1\\)</span>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Si <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x\\ge 1\\)</span>, <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\displaystyle\nf(x)=\\ln\\left(\\frac{x^2+1}{2x}+\\frac{x^2-1}{2x}\\right)=\\ln\nx\\)</span>.</p></li>\n<li><p>Si <span class=\"math inline\">\\(0&lt;x\\le 1\\)</span>, <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\displaystyle\nf(x)=\\ln\\left(\\frac{x^2+1}{2x}+\\frac{1-x^2}{2x}\\right)=\\ln\n\\frac{1}{x}=-\\ln x\\)</span>.</p></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Puisque <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\ln x\\)</span> est positif si\n<span class=\"math inline\">\\(x\\ge 1\\)</span> et négatif si <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(x\\le 1\\)</span>, on obtient dans les deux cas\n<span class=\"math inline\">\\(f(x)=|\\ln x|\\)</span>.</p>\n<div class=\"center\">\n<p><svg version='1.1' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink' width='261.485pt' height='163.956pt' viewBox='0 0 261.485 163.956'><defs><font id='HJGEVI-CMR10' horiz-adv-x='0'><font-face font-family='HJGEVI-CMR10' units-per-em='1000' ascent='750' descent='250'/><glyph unicode='(' horiz-adv-x='388' vert-adv-y='388' glyph-name='parenleft' d='M331-240C331-237 331-235 314-218C189-92 157 97 157 250C157 424 195 598 318 723C331 735 331 737 331 740C331 747 327 750 321 750C311 750 221 682 162 555C111 445 99 334 99 250C99 172 110 51 165-62C225-185 311-250 321-250C327-250 331-247 331-240Z'/><glyph unicode=')' horiz-adv-x='388' vert-adv-y='388' glyph-name='parenright' d='M289 250C289 328 278 449 223 562C163 685 77 750 67 750C61 750 57 746 57 740C57 737 57 735 76 717C174 618 231 459 231 250C231 79 194-97 70-223C57-235 57-237 57-240C57-246 61-250 67-250C77-250 167-182 226-55C277 55 289 166 289 250Z'/><glyph unicode='0' horiz-adv-x='500' vert-adv-y='500' glyph-name='zero' d='M460 320C460 400 455 480 420 554C374 650 292 666 250 666C190 666 117 640 76 547C44 478 39 400 39 320C39 245 43 155 84 79C127-2 200-22 249-22C303-22 379-1 423 94C455 163 460 241 460 320ZM249 0C210 0 151 25 133 121C122 181 122 273 122 332C122 396 122 462 130 516C149 635 224 644 249 644C282 644 348 626 367 527C377 471 377 395 377 332C377 257 377 189 366 125C351 30 294 0 249 0Z'/><glyph unicode='1' horiz-adv-x='500' vert-adv-y='500' glyph-name='one' d='M294 640C294 664 294 666 271 666C209 602 121 602 89 602V571C109 571 168 571 220 597V79C220 43 217 31 127 31H95V0C130 3 217 3 257 3S384 3 419 0V31H387C297 31 294 42 294 79V640Z'/></font><font id='GIYPFW-CMMI10' horiz-adv-x='0'><font-face font-family='GIYPFW-CMMI10' units-per-em='1000' ascent='750' descent='250'/><glyph unico